<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="367" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,764,1376,1574]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">
This species was previously recorded from Zouguépo, Guinean 
<collectingRegion box="[398,478,1411,1437]" country="Liberia" name="Nimba" pageId="8" pageNumber="367">Nimba</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="AELLEN, V." box="[496,657,1411,1437]" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" pagination="629 - 638" refId="ref11916" refString="AELLEN, V. 1963. La Reserve Naturelle Integrale du Mont Nimba. XXIX. Chiropteres. Memoires de l'Institut Francais d'Afrique Noire, 66: 629 - 638." type="journal article" year="1963">Aellen, 1963</bibRefCitation>
). During this survey, it was recorded sparsely in open savanna on the Liberian side of the mountain. This species was easily identifiable by its trifid upper incisors and short ears (
<quantity box="[333,417,1548,1574]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="367" unit="mm" value="21.0">21 mm</quantity>
in DM 12611).
</paragraph>
